snippets.snippet: If you’re in the Osaka Bay area, you are very likely visiting the aquarium or Universal Studios.But if you’re around the aquarium with an extra 15 minutes to spare, consider a ride on the Tempozan Ferris Wheel.
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel - Inside Osaka

snippets.snippet: Tempozan Harbor Village is an entertainment and shopping complex centered on Kaiyukan, one of the world’s largest aquariums. The aquarium, shops offering Osaka souvenir and gift items, restaurants serving Osaka specialties, Ferris wheel, and sightseeing cruises are sure to keep everyone entertained all day. Tempozan Marketplace
snippets.title: Tempozan Harbor Village | Osaka Aquarium KAIYUKAN

snippets.snippet: A 5-minute walk from the Osakako subway station, and steps away from the Kaiyukan aquarium, the Tempozan Ferris Wheel soars 112.5 meters into the air and has a diameter of 100 meters, making it one of the world's largest Ferris wheels.
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel | OSAKA-INFO

snippets.snippet: We recommend booking Tempozan Ferris Wheel tours ahead of time to secure your spot. If you book with Tripadvisor, you can cancel up to 24 hours before your tour starts for a full refund. See all 7 Tempozan Ferris Wheel tours on Tripadvisor
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel (Osaka) - 2020 All You Need to Know ...

snippets.snippet: Tempozan Ferris Wheel opened to the public on July 12, 1997, and was then the tallest Ferris wheel in the world. During the 17-minute ride it offers a view of Osaka Bay and surrounding areas, including Mount Ikoma to the east, Akashi Kaikyō Bridge to the west, Kansai International Airport to the south, and the Rokko Mountains to the north.
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel - Wikipedia

snippets.snippet: Book your tickets online for Tempozan Ferris Wheel, Osaka: See 1,671 reviews, articles, and 1,298 photos of Tempozan Ferris Wheel, ranked No.6 on Tripadvisor among 1,454 attractions in Osaka.
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel (Osaka): UPDATED 2020 All You Need ...

snippets.snippet: Tempozan Ferris Wheel: Sunny Surprises in Osaka, Japan Even before six o’clock, I was already at the foot of the giant spinning wheel to catch the sunset. But I forgot one thing: I was in Japan.
snippets.title: Tempozan Ferris Wheel: Sunny Surprises in Osaka, Japan ...

snippets.snippet: Tempozan Giant Ferris Wheel. We recommend taking a trip to Tempozan Harbor Village when visiting Osaka, especially if you have younger children. The village contains an enormous aquarium, a giant Ferris wheel, Legoland Discovery Center, and lastly, you can even take a bay cruise.
snippets.title: Osaka Guide: Tempozan Harbor Village • Just One Cookbook

snippets.snippet: Before there was the London Eye, there was THE Tempozan Ferris Wheel! Situated at the mouth of the Osaka Bay, Tempozan Ferris Wheel was the biggest, tallest and most technologically advanced observation wheel in the world (it was later surpassed by the gigantic London Eye).

snippets.snippet: A conveyor belt sushi boom started in 1970 after a conveyor belt sushi restaurant served sushi at the Osaka World Expo. Another boom started in 1980, when eating out became more popular, and finally in the late 1990s, when inexpensive restaurants became popular after the burst of the economic bubble.
snippets.title: Conveyor belt sushi - Wikipedia

snippets.snippet: Kaiten-sushi is a fast-food style of sushi from Japan, where plates of sushi revolve around the restaurant on a conveyer belt. Called “kaiten-zushi” in Japanese, the name literally means “rotating sushi”. This is different from conventional sushi restaurants, where customers usually sit at the counter across from the staff and order their sushi directly.

snippets.snippet: The Osaka Aquarium Kaiyukan (海遊館, Kaiyūkan, known as the Kaiyukan) is an aquarium located in the ward of Minato in Osaka, Japan, near Osaka Bay. It is one of the largest public aquariums in the world, and is a member of the Japanese Association of Zoos and Aquariums (JAZA).
